caption: No matter what dish I order there I always enjoy it
Amazing food. Service was also wonderful. Great experience overall.
(Translated by Google) Delicious, but very salty shrimp.  (Original) Вкусно, но очень солёные креветки.

Everything we have tried here is absolutely incredible. Very generous portions and you can it’s made fresh. The staff is extremely kind and service is excellent. They also offer vegan options which are delicious. Cannot recommend enough! Try the grilled veggies as a side they are *chef’s kiss*
Ordered from here last night, and it was absolutely delicious. Use their website to place your order, instead of Grubhub/Seamless!
My whole family loves this place! Great food and service.
Nice food, friendly staff
The food is amazing true authentic Greek cuisine

My go-to is the traditional Greek salad with chicken or lamb gyro on top. Generous portions, great quality good, warm pita bread and comes with olive oil and red wine vinegar which is a must and often missed. Great lunch specials too for when it's a busy day and you don't have time to cook. Friendly staff. I go here at least once a week!
Went in after a long day at work to order for takeout. Portion size is generous and food is really good. The server even gave a free dessert which was delicious. Definitely would go back!

I’ve been here twice now,  its on the expensive side for gyros but they are sooo good and the serving is huge! I’ve ordered the lamb and chicken gyro, which comes with fries and another side (salad, extra fries, etc), service has been great and quick! I even got a free dessert this time! Will definitely be returning again and recommend to anyone looking for some tasty Greek food ❤️

Absolutely awful and overpriced! Ordered the vegan dinner with spicy falafel and pita bread- $18 + $3 for pita What I got was a medium sized salad with a few extra toppings (dolmas and falafel). Falafel was dry and NOT spicy. Tomatoes and onions were not  fresh. Pita was standard store-bought. At least it was warm! Would not recommend to anyone
I’m here by recommendation. Update your hours on google it’s 9:40 but it says 10pm and you’re closed.  Thanks.

One of the best Mediterranean/Greek restaurants in NY. 1. Their tzatziki is _THE_ Ultimate reincarnation of the famous traditional sauce and goes well with anything: forget ketchup, dip your fries in the tzatziki! 2. Amazing burgers & fries: hearty meat patty with variety of toppings, fries are crunchy and on point 👌 3. (Berkshire Pork/ Lamb) Chop and Ribeye: Tasty BUT don't order more cooked than medium, they tend to overcook.
Friendly staff,  good authentic Greek food
Incredibly kind and generous staff, nice selection of wines.

LOVE this place. Ever since we placed our first order on grub hub a few months ago, we’ve been ordering from here at least once a week. Somehow it’s hard to find really good fresh healthy food in Brooklyn, this place does it right every time. And the lemon potatoes are to die for 🤤🤤🤤
If your not happy with using a delivery service, then cancel it. Your not forced to use it.
Tried out this place and it's one of my favorite Greek place in NYC, the lamb gyros and chicken gyros are delicious!
Got the spanakopita and it was the worst I have ever had. Do not recommend.
Food is Delicious
Delicious greek food
Very good Greek food

This is excellent food, excellent service. The Spanikopita is fabulous, the lamb is a very high quality, and the pitas are well balanced and flavorful. Best Greek food in Brooklyn, hands down. Dine in is fun, too. We love it all, but the lamb sticks are a delicious bargain.
Good lunch specials, with friendly table service.
This place has fresh, delicious Greek food and friendly service.  I love the calamari and the octopus with a big Greek salad. Everything is made on demand,  so it's a lot like home cooking.

Sooo glad we tried pitas and sticks .my boyfriend and I went the day after new years and enjoyed it very much .  Authentic style Greek / American food which was served fresh and tasty. The service was great  and the waitress was sweet .  The place is clean and very nicely styled.  Portions are decent sized , and the food was made to order.  All the ingredients were fresh as well.  They serve Greek beers , and American beers and wines , coffees teas and started our order with a nice glass bottle of water which I thought was a very nice touch .  Definitely a place worth going on a date night or just a quiet evening..we will definitely be  back . Thank you
Really delicious and authentic Greek food. From the dips to the meat sampler "pikilia."

They never give the extras that you need - I ordered a salad, it came without dressing, I ordered saganaki, it came without bread, I ordered a souvlaki stick, it came without tsatsiki.  I stopped ordering.
Great warm place... workers great also
First rate Greek food and comfortable to dine in.

This place is THE BEST. Staff is amazing and the food is soooo delicious and well priced. Popped in with my husband and baby only a couple of days ago and am still thinking about it. Definitely order the shrimp saganaki and fresh tzatzini! Drool.
It’s a clean place with crazy good food and the French fries ALWAYS TRY THE FRIES

I eat here or order from this place at least 2 x per week , sometimes more sometimes less . Amazing Greek food , always fresh and warm. One time i had small problem the management fixed in 24 h , and they showed how professional they are to their costumers . I would recommend this place 100% to everyone who enjoys any types of Mediterranean food, it’s healthy, its fresh and its on time .
Delicious food.  We were a large group and they handled us all very well, quickly and friendly!
Very attentive...remembers your food allergies
I very much enjoyed the dishes and customer service, awesome location nearby to my apartment. The employees are always super nice. Highly recommended.

Quality food at a reasonable price. Is it the cheapest kebabs or grilled meats? No, but as the saying goes "you get what you pay for". Everytime I've been to Pitas and Sticks, I never question the quality of the ingredients. I never think to myself "hmm, I think that tasted like lamb". They have all the spinning grillers in plain view so you know the meet is freshly cut off and not taken out of the fridge and microwaved.

Some of the best Greek food I have had. The prices are amazing and the portions are outstanding. The owner and staff are always so friendly and accommodating. Lunch or Dinner it’s worth a stop in or they do a great delivery. It’s always so quick and hot. The happy hour and lunch specials at the place are worth a trip in itself. Really can’t say anything negative about this place. Always a favorite.
Their food is always great! Usually older the mixed grill, sausage, rice, spinach bake, extra pitas. And the baklava here is the bomb, a must try.
Foods always great here!
Great
I enjoyed it as I have several times in the past. Excellent service
Great food at decent prices.
Good food at a good price! Service was excellent.
Excellent menu choices, all well prepared.  Nice touch to Greek salad using blocks of feta. Sit down table service and it was super busy on carryout.
Absolutely delicious fresh food! Everyone I've invited there has enjoyed it..my mom loves the Chicken Soup! Recording Artist-Edwin Vazquez
We've ordered delivery before and loved it!  We were in the neighborhood and stopped in.    So good!  Pitas and grape leaves and fried and grilled calamari.  Very friendly, too!
Great little place for delicious healthy lunch. Excellent grilled calamari.
Great food, love the grilled octopus and Greek salad. Friendly staff, good place to eat and relax.
Love the food there fast & Good Service

If i could, i would give this place 3.5 stars.  My lamb platter was pretty good, so i will round up.  My daughter had the chicken which she did not care for.  I would go here again, but you can do better if you go into the city.  Wife did like the lemon potatoes.  Like most small places, they don't give enough pita.

had the falafel platter as order out. you do get a nice sized salad that could be it’s own meal. however the rice was irredeemable, i threw the whole tin out; falafel was the disc type and very dry/under seasoned; tzatziki sauce barely made it edible. Also confusing as to why you only get four pitas if you order whole wheat but get a fist sized stack when you order regular pitas (probably around 10+). Hoping the baklava is good to make up for everything.
Really good traditional Greek food!
Never showed up. Called them 5 times. Was fed misinformation each time. Avoid
Best Greek food in Brooklyn hands down
Great staff, great food, great price point. Can't beat that.
Lamb chops are great, the flavor will send you to Heaven.  For an authentic Greek meal with good service, I highly recommend it.
Excellent food excellent service
Amazing authentic Greek food. Definitely a place to go if you are looking for Greek cuisine. Would be coming back in the near future for another delicious meal.

Real time Greek food for real time people. Pita and sticks is the truth when it comes to Greek cuisine. They ain’t gonna do you wrong. The tzechi (spelling) sauce is top 5 in NYC and made right. The staff - friendly. The food - amazing. The tables - standard. You go here they’re gonna make sure you leave happy.  DIZZZZZURT. Dessert is clutch here too. Dunno if they have dessert on their normal menu, but they had it on a special and it was pretty dang amazin

Fresh gyro is the way to go. I havent been here in a while but it came up in my review list. When I went the pitas were awesome, the sauce was great and everythign was fresh....mmm..now I think Im going to have to go back more sooner than I thought.
nice place to grab a quick bite.
Love going here with my family. Reasonable price and friendly staff
Love this place! I’m a regular at least 2-3x/ week. Everything is fresh!
loved the food and atmosphere was very friendly I will be going back for more
Good food, nice atmosphere. Just remember to repeat your order, because at times staff doesn't capture everything while taking orders. Love the frappe

Amazing food! We had this catered for a work meeting and it was a big hit! The entire team had something to eat and wanted seconds.  I would highly recommend for catering. Delicious cacik, chicken kebab, and spinach pie.
Love the food :)

Looks nice and clean, Spinach pastry was too soggy inside and the flavor was just ok.. salad didn't taste fresh and quite skimpy on the feta.. chicken and beef sticks were done well, but nothing exciting, no spice ..tzaziki a lil bland.. pita felt warmed in a micro.. french fries were done well. Prices a high for what you get, mediocre and boring for me. service IS nice.
Happy hour apps, food is good and fast. Kid friendly
spicy feta

This place is honestly delicious. Warm pita, hummus, and gyros: what’s not to love? The server was friendly and fast and the price, while a little high, was well worth it for the food. Would recommend
Some of the best food. Service was too notch.  They the calamari and octopus.

The food was delicious! I am very picky with food and it is very rare that I clean my plate. I cleaned my plate and picked from my husbands plate. I will be returning! I found the prices to be reasonable too.

Pretty amazing. You should know the lamb is Cubed, not shaved. And they add FF, a la Souvlaki King Truck in Astoria. That being said, I only give it 4.9 stars(just kidding) because it should be $7 in my opinion, but we are in Park Slope, and it is a brick n mortar store. My single true recommendation, I’d love a legit Mediterranean hot sauce instead of Franks or Cholula or whatever i got. But this was a Damn Good Gyro(pronounced Yee-Ro) and i highly recommend this place.  Best of luck guys n gals, you’ll see me often.
Great deal lunch special, rotisserie meat over Greek salad is a great deal
Good food but can be a little salty in some dishes. Excellent calamari (fried and grilled) and octopus.  Very friendly and patient service. Great for families.
THE WORST DELIVERY ever!!! Always have to wait for my food for almost 2hrs! Added 1 star only because food is pretty good.
I go there quite often. I usually get  the pork souvlaki and they have never disappointed me .The meat is always delicious.  The saganaki is very good.
Very good spot,good food,prices are right
Excellent authentic Greek food. Gives me memories of my time spent in Greecd.

This place made me a lamb lover! Seriously, I hated lamb all my life and the halal truck was my definition of tasty lamb (eye roll) But at my co-worker's suggestion I had a Greek salad with lamb and it changed my life! And the accompanying white pita bread was delicious. The wheat version leaves a bitter after taste. I'll never eat lamb from a truck again lol. Haven't tried anything else yet.
Love this place. Good food. The people that run it are great.
My favorite greek restaurant in nyc. Everything here is good. Finally went in after years of ordering delivery. Table service was delightful and the food was even hotter!
What a pleasant surprise. My wife and I stopped in for a quick bite and it was delicious. Service is superb and the decor is great
Delicious Greek food,comfortable atmosphere no rush, my favorite μουσακάς is the best, and many other delicious platters at reasonable prices!! Highly recommend!!
Awesome food
Excellent staff quick service and Super Great Tasting  Food!!! I loved the mixed platter with Greek French Fries salad all in one Platter and Horta!!!
Love this place
Lamb chops on point
Good price and a lot of flavors. Love it.
Great food and prices! The pitas are really good! Can't wait to go here again!

Haven't ever been disappointed by a meal here. From the various sticks to the generously sized entrees to the half-priced appetizers at happy hour - even their chicken fingers. Everything is wonderful. Decor is lovely and comfortable, never felt rushed even on a busy evening.

It has a few good dishes on the menu, but the selection is limited, and the price is not competitive. The decor in the restaurant is chic, but space is small, having few customers eat there at meal time  doesn't create a great atmosphere.
The lunch specials are WORTH every $1. Delicious and fresh food.
Quiet place with cozy interior. Delicious Greek food at a reasonable price. Definitely recommend for your next night out.
Great service and good food!!!
Lunch deal is great!
great spanakopita, calamari, pitas, and a $20 bottle of wine. excited to return.
My favorite lunch spot the best falafels pita bread and stuffed grapes!!!

Great little Greek restaurant. LOVE their atherina... it's an app of fried little fish. It's as addictive as French fries but fish. Always fried perfectly,  never greasy. Enough  to share. Also great spanikopita, their lemon potatoes are amazing, avgolemono soup is wonderful... I don't get over there often enough.  I've never been disappointed by the quality of the food.
Bad kitchen exhaust
Love this place for quick bites on a stick. SALMON sticks are murder.
So delicious!
Great food, great service, as accommodating as they can possibly be with food allergies.
Best souvlaki & gyro in NY
Great Greek gyros!
Very hard to chew souvlaki pork meat, long wait, side order of boiled potatoes was $7.
Clean. Yummy. Friendly.
Fresh, delicious and authentic! The owner is super nice, prices are fair for park slope and the food is super tasty. Very fresh made on the spot nothing frozen or packaged. Will be back.

Excellent food and fast delivery. A bit pricey, but the platters come with a large amount of fries or rice and a large Greek salad. you can easily get 1-2 meals out of it, and there's a nice selection of sides and dessert (the semolina custard cake being my personal favorite).
The food is great.
Me and my other half love Pita and Sticks.. the food is amazing!!  Everything on the menu!! Blue moon on tap!! Yessir
This is my go to for work catering. They are so reliable and delicious - even when catering for up to 50 people. HIGHLY recommend!!!!!
It was simply superb; inexpensive and amazing food that doesn't leave you feeling gross. What a great find! Give it a shot--you'll be as happy as I am.
Food was GREAT
Food and service was great. Nothing wowed me but I would go back again.
Food was delicious. Had a traditional gyro, the meat platter and the souvlaki platter. Wish the lemon potatoes were cooked longer and had a crisp to them. Rice pudding is a MUST HAVE!
Excellent food. Highly recommend the mixed platter. Great salad as well
Great food. And very nice service!
Great Quick Real Greek. eat here
Great moussaka and dips
Food was great!
Fun Greek restaurant, specializing in kebobs.
I've had the whole "Greek food" idea. A simple gyro or Greek salad, but this place was the truth! If you are a meat lover , try the special "Bifteki." Exquisite!
order from there all the time love it
Delicious!
One of my favorite spots in Park Slope. The chicken, pork, and shrimp pitas are on the money. Their Greek fries are good to go too. The waitresses are always pleasant and attentive.
Not bad
Very good food and service the tap os also great
5 stars for great food and service
Excellent lamb
Super phenomenal
The best greek food in Park Slope!! Try the mixed grill platter to get a taste of everything!
Very impressed with the food quality and great service. Best Greek restaurant in brooklyn!!
Food is tasty and service is superb

I've never had Greek food before....but this place is AMAZING! From the exceptional service and from the hostess to the manager, to the delicious and filling food. I now LOVE Greek cuisine! I would recommend this place ten times over. Will also be ordering for take out. You won't regret visiting this restaurant.
Extremely friendly staff. Very helpful when we asked questions about the menu. The food is superb.

Finally went to eat here and I'm hooked. Happy hour during the week from 2-5 is awesome. The food is delicious. The lamb is tender, the roasted veggies are perfect. We love their spanakopita. Not salty as some others I've had. My husband loves their falafel which I've tried and must agree with him. We are also rice pudding snobs and this is one of the best. Just like my moms. I want to eventually try everything on their menu. This is a must go to restaurant in the slope. Enjoy!
Rude driver
Had the lamb burger sliders from the lunch menu, and was happily surprised by the quality. I will definitely return.
Very good lunch place. Tasty Authentic Greek Food.  You'll enjoy!

Im a new customer, I liked the food hated the service, mainly because it takes almost and hour and a half every single time I ordered. Today I ordered a 24 dollar steak and 2 cans of soda. After waiting an hour and a half for my steak. The barely polite driver tells me he forgot my sodas or "they" forgot my sodas . I was furious but willing to compromise so I asked him to please just got to the store and get me my 2 sodas so I dont have to delay any longer and he says no, he has to go back to the store and get it, which meant most likely another hour of waiting.  I don't know about the intelligence of any of this. So. I have him back his food and told him to forget it. I was stunned by how unprofessional and odd this was. I guess he just wanted to make it hard for me  to get those sodas, or assumed I would just take the steak and be fine without my drinks. Well, what really sealed the deal was when I called the manager and let him know how furious I was he hung up in my face which only confirmed that these people are NOT the kind of people I would ever consider trusting to make my food, or spend another dime on. Good luck.

Huge portion and delicious!!! We both got platter sized meals. Hubby loved the fries, I really enjoyed the rice and the lamb gyro was amazing- tons of meat! Great service as well. Cool environment, simple and clean. Nice place for delicious Greek food!

I was kind of amazed how good their sandwiches were. I got the pork, chicken, lamb sampler as wraps and shared the dip platter with my wife. Really awesome. Any place that puts french fries on its sandwiches gets it.  We ordered delivery and happily didn't have any issues-the food came fresh and the pita was still warm.

called for delivery at 7:10pm after being on hold for 5min..was told delivery would take 30min..no food...called again at 8:11pm and was told 5-7min..still no food..called again at 8:37pm & was told "any minute..trouble with delivery person"..still no food!! It is now 8:53pm. NO FOOD & No callback from restaurant with any status update on our food. No offer to comp meal at this point either. Will NEVER try this place again after this horrendous customer non-service.

Horrible horrible horrible delivery service! Been waiting 1:50 minutes for food that was told would take 30 mins. Called several times and got a BS story, "be there in 5 minutes", "be there in a few seconds". Unreal!  Don't waste your time ordering from here. Welcome to Park Slope Pitas and Sticks, land of many restaurants where you will not last 6 months.
Soo I'm not sure how the food is because I never got the food delivered. Spent 2 hrs waiting on the food. Not a very happy camper.

The food is really really good. The mixed platters are delicious, the Greek salads are made with care (really high quality ingredients), and the beef stew with orzo was flavorful, homey, and filling. The setting is very casual, wooden tables and chairs, a few tables with stools and they offer beer and wine as well. If you don't have time, order in advance and carry out.
The food was absolutely amazing. Attentive service, warm atmosphere, and very moderately priced. Can't recommend it highly enough.
